<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E69FCD3FF3BFA96C411" blockId="40.[826,1441,198,587]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCD3FF3BFC16C681" box="[826,922,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Identity:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD58B8FF831E69FC4DFF3BFA90C686" author="Bossuyt F &amp; Dubois A" box="[932,1308,198,220]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref42998" refString="Bossuyt F, Dubois A. 2001. A review of the frog genus Philautus Gistel, 1848 (Amphibia, Anura, Ranidae, Rhacophorinae). Zeylanica 6: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2001">Bossuyt &amp; Dubois (2001: 14–15)</bibRefCitation>
provided a detailed review on the nomenclatural history, and considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FC20FEFEFAEDC743" authority="Boulenger (1882)" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1882" box="[969,1377,259,281]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulcher">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FC20FEFEFBF6C742" box="[969,1146,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Ixalus pulcher</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD58B8FF831E69FB66FEFEFAEDC743" author="Boulenger GA" box="[1167,1377,259,281]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" refId="ref43127" refString="Boulenger GA. 1882. Catalogue of the Batrachia Salientia s. Ecaudata in the collection of the British Museum. London: Taylor &amp; Francis." type="book" year="1882">Boulenger (1882)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FCD3FEDFFB64C76D" authority="Ahl, 1927" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1927" box="[826,1256,290,312]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rhacophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrimus">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCD3FEDFFBFCC76D" box="[826,1136,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Rhacophorus pulcherrimus</emphasis>
Ahl, 1927
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FCD3FEBDFB55C70C" authority="Gunther, 1876" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1876" box="[826,1241,320,342]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCD3FEBDFB96C70F" box="[826,1050,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Ixalus glandulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD58B8FF831E69FBC3FEBDFB55C70C" author="Gunther A" box="[1066,1241,320,342]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="567 - 577" refId="ref43526" refString="Gunther A. 1876. Third report on collections of Indian reptiles obtained by the British Museum. Proceedings of Zoological Society 1875: 567 - 577." type="journal article" year="1876">Günther, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD58B8FF831E69FC21FEA2FB12C72F" author="Jerdon TC" box="[968,1182,351,373]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="1486 - 1488" refId="ref43806" refString="Jerdon TC. 1853. Catalogue of reptiles inhabiting the Peninsula of India (continued from p. 479). Journal of Asiatic Society of Bengal 1870: 1486 - 1488." type="journal article" year="1853">Jerdon (1853: 533)</bibRefCitation>
stated the snout–vent length as roughly 
<quantity id="4CA488ACFF831E69FBE5FE80FBFDC7C9" box="[1036,1137,381,403]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="30.5">30.5 mm</quantity>
, and described the unique yellowish colour on the side and limbs (
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF831E69FB10FE61FAC6C7E8" box="[1273,1354,412,434]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1359,1378]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-545@40.[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 34. Neotype of Ixalus glandulosus (BMNH 1947.2.27.22) from ‘Manantavadi’ (i.e. Mananthavady)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445426/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
), which exactly matches with the yellow forelimbs and lateral region of the 
<typeStatus id="54E79BEBFF831E69FC3DFE27FBA1C7B5" box="[980,1069,474,495]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FBBBFE27FB4CC7B4" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1882" box="[1106,1216,473,495]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulcher">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FBBBFE27FB4CC7B4" box="[1106,1216,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">I. pulcher</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which presently is the 
<typeStatus id="54E79BEBFF831E69FC83FE05FC4FC457" box="[874,963,504,525]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FC04FE04FB1EC457" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1876" box="[1005,1170,504,526]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FC04FE04FB1EC457" box="[1005,1170,504,526]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">I. glandulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Jerdon attributed the species epithet presumably because of its prominently granular (‘glandular’) yellow lateral side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E69FCD3FD8EFC74C5C6" blockId="40.[826,1442,626,1199]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCD3FD8EFB59C4DD" box="[826,1237,626,648]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FC2FFD8FFB59C4DD" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[966,1237,626,647]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">Philautus glandulosus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from known congeners by the following combination of characters: (1) medium male adult size (SVL 25.2 ± 2.0 mm, 
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FBD5FD32FBDCC4BE" box="[1084,1104,719,740]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">N</emphasis>
= 4); (2) snout pointed; (3) head length shorter than width, HW 10.0 ± 
<quantity id="4CA488ACFF831E69FAACFD10FA10C558" box="[1349,1436,749,771]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, HL 9.2 ± 
<quantity id="4CA488ACFF831E69FC43FCF6FB8DC57B" box="[938,1025,779,801]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FBF8FCF1FBA9C57B" box="[1041,1061,780,801]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">N</emphasis>
= 4; (4) dorsum shagreened; (5) lateral abdominal area prominently glandular; (6) fingertips rounded; (7) dorsal surface of forearm and loreal region yellow; (8) anterior and posterior surface of thighs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E69FCBAFC59FC1EC2F5" blockId="40.[826,1442,626,1199]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FCBAFC59FBD5C5E3" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[851,1113,932,953]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCBAFC59FBD5C5E3" box="[851,1113,932,953]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Philautus glandulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sole Western Ghats species in the genus with an invariable yellow dorsal surface of forearm and loreal region in life, and creamy white or yellowish in preservation (
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF831E69FADCFBFDFA11C24F" box="[1333,1437,1024,1046]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="38.[164,243,1842,1861]" captionTargetBox="[185,1422,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-0@38.[182,1425,194,1813]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Figure 31. Distribution map. A, Philautus dubois; B, map showing Malabar (shaded in grey), from which the type of Philautus flaviventris was collected; C, Philautus glandulosus; D, Philautus graminirupes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445420/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Figs 31C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF831E69FCD3FBE2FCD4C26E" box="[826,856,1055,1076]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1359,1378]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-545@40.[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 34. Neotype of Ixalus glandulosus (BMNH 1947.2.27.22) from ‘Manantavadi’ (i.e. Mananthavady)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445426/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF831E69FC83FBE3FC04C26E" box="[874,904,1054,1076]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,1454,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-558@40.[168,777,1454,1823]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 35. Philautus glandulosus: a specimen from Mananthavady (SDB 40239)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445428/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">35</figureCitation>
). It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FB55FBE2FACBC26E" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2005" box="[1212,1351,1055,1076]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bobingeri">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FB55FBE2FACBC26E" box="[1212,1351,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. bobingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FA64FBE2FC2DC209" authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jayarami" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FA64FBE2FC2DC209" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. jayarami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B4420FF831E69FC45FBC3FB8AC209" box="[940,1030,1086,1107]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which it resembles well in overall appearance (
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF831E69FC27FBA1FB9DC228" box="[974,1041,1116,1138]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[164,243,799,818]" captionTargetBox="[423,1184,200,767]" captionTargetId="figure-502@8.[419,1187,197,770]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Morphometric distinction between males of four green Philautus species: Z, Philautus akroparallagi sp. nov.; -, Philautus bobingeri; O, Philautus glandulosus; and •, Philautus jayarami sp. nov. The ratio of the snout length (SL)/eye length (EL) is plotted against the snout–vent length SVL (see Table 2)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445368/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). For differences with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FAF0FBA1FA2DC22B" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2005" box="[1305,1441,1116,1137]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bobingeri">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FAF0FBA1FA2DC22B" box="[1305,1441,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. bobingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FC9AFB86FC77C2CA" authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" box="[883,1019,1147,1168]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jayarami" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FC9AFB86FC77C2CA" box="[883,1019,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. jayarami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B4420FF831E69FBE0FB86FBEBC2CA" box="[1033,1127,1147,1168]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, see ‘comparison’ of those species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E69FCD3FB2AFAB9C373" blockId="40.[826,1441,1238,1322]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCD3FB2AFBFEC2B6" box="[826,1138,1238,1260]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
Description of the 
<typeStatus id="54E79BEBFF831E69FBFEFB2AFBE0C2B6" box="[1047,1132,1239,1260]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">neotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
A detailed description of the 
<typeStatus id="54E79BEBFF831E69FC99FB08FC45C350" box="[880,969,1269,1290]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">neotype</typeStatus>
was published in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD58B8FF831E69FB29FB08FC09C370" author="Bossuyt F &amp; Dubois A" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref42998" refString="Bossuyt F, Dubois A. 2001. A review of the frog genus Philautus Gistel, 1848 (Amphibia, Anura, Ranidae, Rhacophorinae). Zeylanica 6: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2001">Bossuyt &amp; Dubois (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. Measurements are given in 
<tableCitation id="C6DE10F2FF831E69FB35FAEEFABDC373" box="[1244,1329,1299,1321]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="10.[113,177,400,421]" captionText="Table 2. Morphometric measurements (in mm) of the specimens used in this study" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2375C1FF831E69FF4DFAB2FD61C325" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445426" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5445426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445426/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" startId="40.[164,243,1359,1378]" targetBox="[168,777,888,1329]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E69FF4DFAB2FD61C325" blockId="40.[164,779,1359,1407]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FF4DFAB2FE95C338" bold="true" box="[164,281,1359,1378]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Figure 34.</emphasis>
Neotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FE2DFAB2FD12C338" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1876" box="[452,670,1359,1378]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FE2DFAB2FD12C338" box="[452,670,1359,1378]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Ixalus glandulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BMNH 1947.2.27.22) from ‘Manantavadi’ (i.e. Mananthavady).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E68FCD3FAACFEC4C76D" blockId="40.[826,1441,1360,1903]" lastBlockId="41.[144,758,198,312]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="415" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FCD3FAACFC64C33C" box="[826,1000,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Colour in life:</emphasis>
BNHS 4453 (in the wild), dorsum uniform dark green with a few scattered light-brown spots, lateral side yellow, loreal and tympanic regions yellow, iris reddish brown encircled by a thin bluish outer ring, forelimb yellow with a few dark-grey spots, thigh with a green line extending from dorsum to knee, anterior and posterior margins yellow, without markings, tibia almost completely green, tarsus yellow with a few scattered dark-greyish green spots; ventral side light yellow, throat, hands, and feet light yellow (
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF831E69FBFEF97EFBF6C0C3" box="[1047,1146,1667,1689]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="38.[164,243,1842,1861]" captionTargetBox="[185,1422,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-0@38.[182,1425,194,1813]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Figure 31. Distribution map. A, Philautus dubois; B, map showing Malabar (shaded in grey), from which the type of Philautus flaviventris was collected; C, Philautus glandulosus; D, Philautus graminirupes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445420/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Fig. 31C</figureCitation>
). In captivity (either in collection bags or in terrarium), this frog has the ability to change the dorsal green colour to dark purple or violet; however, the pattern is reliably constant. 
<accessionNumber id="940FB8AAFF831E69FC63F900FB9DC148" box="[906,1041,1789,1810]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/SDB40239" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">SDB 40239</accessionNumber>
(in captivity), dorsum uniformly dark purple, without markings, lateral side yellow, loreal and tympanic regions yellow, forelimb yellow, thigh with a purple line extending from dorsum to knee, anterior and posterior margins yellow, without markings, tibia almost completely purple, tarsus yellow; ventral side yellowish, throat, hands, and feet yellow (
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF821E68FF03FEDFFEB7C76D" box="[234,315,289,312]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,1454,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-558@40.[168,777,1454,1823]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 35. Philautus glandulosus: a specimen from Mananthavady (SDB 40239)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445428/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2375C1FF831E69FF4DF8C0FE56C134" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445428" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5445428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445428/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" startId="40.[164,243,1853,1872]" targetBox="[168,777,1454,1823]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF831E69FF4DF8C0FE56C134" blockId="40.[164,779,1853,1902]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FF4DF8C0FE95C10A" bold="true" box="[164,281,1853,1872]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Figure 35.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5C5ECAFF831E69FECFF8C0FDAEC10A" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[294,546,1853,1872]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF831E69FECFF8C0FDAEC10A" box="[294,546,1853,1872]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Philautus glandulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: a specimen from Mananthavady (SDB 40239).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF821E68FF79FE9EFE6FC7CC" blockId="41.[144,759,354,407]" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF821E68FF79FE9EFE8CC722" box="[144,256,355,376]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Variation:</emphasis>
Measurements of 
<specimenCount id="9D5AEEC0FF821E68FE3EFE9FFD0FC722" box="[471,643,354,376]" pageId="41" pageNumber="415" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
including 
<typeStatus id="54E79BEBFF821E68FF79FE7CFF65C7CC" box="[144,233,385,406]" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">neotype</typeStatus>
are given in 
<tableCitation id="C6DE10F2FF821E68FE60FE7CFE52C7CC" box="[393,478,385,407]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="10.[113,177,400,421]" captionText="Table 2. Morphometric measurements (in mm) of the specimens used in this study" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE32549FF821E68FF79FE3CFDB9C553" blockId="41.[144,759,449,777]" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B928F95BFF821E68FF79FE3CFD80C78C" box="[144,524,449,470]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Distribution and natural history:</emphasis>
Mananthavady and Sulthanbathery of 
<collectingRegion id="4998EBABFF821E68FE8EFE1DFE3BC7AC" box="[359,439,480,502]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Kerala</collectingRegion>
, and Mercara in 
<collectingRegion id="4998EBABFF821E68FD93FE1DFD7AC7AC" box="[634,758,480,502]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="136739CCFF821E68FF71FE02FF77C44E" box="[152,251,511,533]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="38.[164,243,1842,1861]" captionTargetBox="[185,1422,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-0@38.[182,1425,194,1813]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Figure 31. Distribution map. A, Philautus dubois; B, map showing Malabar (shaded in grey), from which the type of Philautus flaviventris was collected; C, Philautus glandulosus; D, Philautus graminirupes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445420/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Fig. 31C</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="C6DE10F2FF821E68FEFAFE02FEE9C44F" box="[275,357,511,533]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Collection localities that are discussed in the text. Localities are arranged by state" pageId="41" pageNumber="415">Table 1</tableCitation>
). This species strongly prefers vegetation layers above 
<quantity id="4CA488ACFF821E68FE5BFDE0FE50C469" box="[434,476,541,563]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="415" unit="m" value="4.0">4 m</quantity>
in height. In Wayanad this species was located either from the rainforest canopy (about 10-m high in Mananthavady) or in forest fringes near coffee plantations (about 4-m high in Sulthanbathery). In Mercara it was observed in an isolated tree in a garden at heights above 
<specimenCount id="9D5AEEC0FF821E68FD91FD4BFD26C496" box="[632,682,694,716]" pageId="41" pageNumber="415" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CA488ACFF821E68FD91FD4BFD2AC496" box="[632,678,694,716]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="415" unit="m" value="4.0">4 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
Specimens were located by their calls, and were collected during rainy evenings after 20:00 h.
</paragraph>
